  "local_port": 39980,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I report fake app on Appstore?",
  "response": "To report a fake app on the App Store, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the App Store**: Launch the App Store on your device.\n\n2. **Find the App**: Search for the app you believe to be fake and open its page.\n\n3. **Scroll Down**: Scroll down to the bottom of the app's page until you see the \"Report a Problem\" button.\n\n4. **Report a Problem**: Tap on \"Report a Problem.\"\n\n5. **Sign In**: You may be prompted to sign in with your Apple ID. Enter your credentials to proceed.\n\n6. **Select a Problem**: You will be taken to a new page where you can select the type of problem you want to report. Choose the most appropriate option, such as \"Report a Fraudulent App\" or \"Report a Copyright Infringement.\"\n\n7. **Provide Details**: Follow the on-screen instructions to provide more details about why you believe the app is fake. You may need to fill out a form explaining the issue.\n\n8. **Submit**: After completing the form, submit your report.\n\nAdditionally, you can also report the app directly to Apple through their official website:\n\n1. **Visit Apple's Report a Problem Page**: Go to `reportaproblem.apple.com`.\n\n2. **Sign In**: Sign in with your Apple ID.\n\n3. **Select the App**: Choose the app you want to report from the list of your purchases or search for it.\n\n4. **Choose the Reason**: Select the reason for reporting the app, such as \"This is a fraudulent app.\"\n\n5. **Explain the Issue**: Provide a detailed explanation of why you believe the app is fake.\n\n6. **Submit the Report**: Submit your report.\n\nBy following these steps, you help Apple become aware of potentially harmful or fake apps, contributing to a safer App Store environment.",
